  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Kitchen Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Central Kitchen Operations Executive – Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct regular visits to customer sites to ensure smooth and consistent operations.</li><li>Liaise with clients to gather operational feedback, address concerns, and identify areas for service and process improvement.</li><li>Investigate customer complaints, QC failures, or operational incidents</li><li>Review, adjust, and optimize operational workflows to improve efficiency and resolve operational issues when required.</li><li>Perform quality control (QC) checks within the central kitchen to ensure compliance with food safety, hygiene, and quality standards.</li><li>Monitor adherence to standard operating procedures (SOPs) across kitchen and delivery operations.</li><li>Prepare and maintain accurate documentation, including QC records, operational reports, corrective action logs, and compliance checklists.</li><li>Monitor inventory levels of raw materials, packaging, and consumables</li><li>Coordinate with procurement and suppliers to prevent shortages or overstocking</li><li>Support continuous improvement initiatives to enhance product quality, operational consistency, and customer satisfaction.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Education & Experience</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum 1–3 years of experience in central kitchen, food manufacturing, catering, or F&B operations</p></li><li><p>Experience in QC, food production, or operations support is an advantage<br /><br /><strong>Personal Attributes</strong></p><ul><li><p>Willingness to travel to customer sites and kitchen facilities as required</p></li><li><p>Hands-on, proactive, and operationally driven</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and as part of a team</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working in a fast-paced, operational environment</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
